- J'ai aussi commencé une app Solo Learning pour avoir des sources différentes sur React 

### Solo learn

React :
- developped by Facebook
- Fast : Compared to other libraries tha manipulate the Dom, React uses a virtual DOM, allowing to update only the parts of the website that have changed
- Ease to use : making building and maintaining large scale applications much less complex

Terminal :
npx create-react-app my-app (my-app étant le nom du dossier qu'on créer)
cd my-app
npm start

Folder:
- public : whatever the end-user see, logos, images, index.html
- src : js, css, index.js, app.js :file is the main component that will be rendered to the DOM

Element: 
- ReactDOM.render (
    <p> I am learnning React </p>,
    document.getElementById('test'));
    
Index.js:
- import React from 'react';
- import ReactDOM from 'react-dom';
- import './style.css';l

Redux :
- 
- store
- connect
- reducer 
